# Manual QA checklist

- [ ] Disconnect Wi-Fi mid-flow → OfflineCard with pre-filled WhatsApp fallback.
- [ ] Submit valid form with backend down → 1st failure: just toast. 2nd failure: toast + WhatsApp fallback.
- [ ] Submit with invalid phone "abc" → highlight phone field, inline error.
- [ ] Submit a moto with car service → bounce back to service step, toast.
- [ ] Submit at slot starting in 30 min → bounce back to time step, toast.
- [ ] Burst submit 6 times → 429 with countdown.
- [ ] WhatsApp deep-link opens with all the booking data pre-filled.
- [ ] When staff_contact.available=false (admin hasn't configured): WhatsApp fallback uses the hardcoded default.

# Acceptance criteria

- [ ] Every documented error_code maps to a specific UX outcome.
- [ ] No infinite spinners.
- [ ] Per-field errors highlight the right field.
- [ ] OfflineCard renders + includes WhatsApp fallback when data is sufficient.
- [ ] WhatsApp fallback emerges after 2 consecutive 5xx or 3 consecutive timeouts.
- [ ] 429 disables submit for Retry-After seconds (visible countdown).
- [ ] All i18n keys present in FR + AR.
- [ ] Manual QA checklist passes.

# Context

The Bookings tab in `mobile-app/screens.jsx` currently shows hardcoded mock entries. Wire it to fetch via `api.getMyBookings()` AND let the customer tap a row to see full details with actionable CTAs: Add to Calendar, Book again, Share via WhatsApp, Contact support.

# Scope — Bookings tab (list view)

In `BookingsScreen` (screens.jsx around line 230):

```js
function BookingsScreen({ t, dir, lang, isActive, openBooking, staffContact }) {
  const [bookings, setBookings] = useS_h([]);
  const [state, setState] = useS_h("loading");
  const [selectedRef, setSelectedRef] = useS_h(null);

  useEffect(() => {
    if (!isActive) return;
    let alive = true;
    setState("loading");
    if (!navigator.onLine) { setState("offline"); return; }
    EwashAPI.getMyBookings()
      .then((resp) => {
        if (!alive) return;
        EwashLog.info("bookings.list", { count: resp.bookings.length });
        if (!resp.bookings.length) { setState("empty"); return; }
        setBookings(resp.bookings);
        setState("list");
      })
      .catch((err) => {
        if (!alive) return;
        EwashLog.warn("bookings.list.error", { error_code: err.error_code, status: err.status });
        if (err.error_code === "no_local_token" || err.error_code === "invalid_token") {
          if (err.error_code === "invalid_token") {
            try { localStorage.removeItem("ewash.bookings_token"); } catch {}
          }
          setState("no_token");
          return;
        }
        setState("error");
      });
    return () => { alive = false; };
  }, [isActive]);

  if (selectedRef) {
    const booking = bookings.find(b => b.ref === selectedRef);
    return (
      <BookingDetailModal
        booking={booking}
        onClose={() => setSelectedRef(null)}
        t={t} dir={dir} lang={lang}
        staffContact={staffContact}
        openBooking={openBooking}
      />
    );
  }

  // ... render by state ...
}
```

# State-by-state UX

| State | UX | Action |
|-------|----|----|
| `loading` | Skeleton: 3 pulsing card placeholders | wait |
| `list` | List of tappable cards (with localized status badges) | tap → detail modal |
| `empty` | "Aucune réservation" + icon | CTA: "Réserver maintenant" |
| `no_token` | "Réservez votre premier lavage pour suivre vos rendez-vous ici" + CTA | CTA: "Commencer" → opens booking flow |
| `error` | "Impossible de charger vos réservations" + retry button | retry → refetch |
| `offline` | OfflineCard | wait for online |

# Booking detail modal (NEW)

```jsx
function BookingDetailModal({ booking, onClose, t, dir, lang, staffContact, openBooking }) {
  const localStatusLabel = t.statusLabels[booking.status] || booking.status_label || booking.status;
  return (
    <Sheet onClose={onClose} dir={dir} title={booking.ref}>
      <header className="booking-detail-header">
        <h2>{booking.ref}</h2>
        <StatusBadge status={booking.status} label={localStatusLabel} />
      </header>
      <dl className="booking-detail-fields">
        <dt>{t.bookings.service}</dt><dd>{booking.service_label}</dd>
        <dt>{t.bookings.vehicle}</dt><dd>{booking.vehicle_label}</dd>
        <dt>{t.bookings.date}</dt><dd>{booking.date_label}</dd>
        <dt>{t.bookings.time}</dt><dd>{booking.slot_label}</dd>
        <dt>{t.bookings.location}</dt><dd>{booking.location_label}</dd>
        <dt>{t.bookings.total}</dt><dd>{booking.total_price_dh} DH</dd>
      </dl>
      <footer className="booking-detail-actions">
        {/* PRIMARY ACTIONS — most-likely customer needs */}
        {_canAddToCalendar(booking) && (
          <Btn onClick={() => { EwashCalendar.download(booking, lang); EwashLog.info("bookings.detail.calendar", { ref: booking.ref }); }} variant="ghost">
            <Icon name="calendar-plus" /> {t.bookings.addToCalendar}
          </Btn>
        )}
        <Btn onClick={() => _shareWhatsApp(booking, t, staffContact)} variant="ghost">
          <Icon name="share" /> {t.bookings.shareViaWhatsApp}
        </Btn>
        {/* SECONDARY ACTIONS — re-engagement */}
        {_canBookAgain(booking) && (
          <Btn onClick={() => { EwashLog.info("bookings.detail.book_again", { ref: booking.ref, service_id: booking.service_id }); openBooking({ prefill: { category: booking.category_id, service_id: booking.service_id } }); }} variant="ghost">
            <Icon name="repeat" /> {t.bookings.bookAgain}
          </Btn>
        )}
        {/* CONTACT */}
        {staffContact?.available && (
          <Btn onClick={() => _contactSupport(booking, staffContact)} variant="ghost">
            <Icon name="message-circle" /> {t.bookings.contactSupport}
          </Btn>
        )}
        <Btn onClick={onClose} variant="primary">{t.close}</Btn>
      </footer>
    </Sheet>
  );
}

function _canAddToCalendar(booking) {
  // Don't show for completed / cancelled / refunded / no_show.
  const inert = new Set(["customer_cancelled", "admin_cancelled", "expired", "no_show", "completed", "completed_with_issue", "refunded"]);
  return !inert.has(booking.status);
}

function _canBookAgain(booking) {
  // Show for anything past the present (basically: not draft, not active).
  const reusable = new Set(["completed", "completed_with_issue", "customer_cancelled", "admin_cancelled", "expired", "no_show"]);
  return reusable.has(booking.status);
}

function _shareWhatsApp(booking, t, staffContact) {
  const phone = staffContact?.whatsapp_phone || "+212611204502";  // fallback hardcoded default
  const text = `Bonjour, ma réservation Ewash ${booking.ref} le ${booking.date_label} à ${booking.slot_label}. Pouvez-vous me donner plus d'infos ?`;
  const url = `https://wa.me/${phone.replace(/[^0-9]/g, "")}?text=${encodeURIComponent(text)}`;
  EwashLog.info("bookings.share", { ref: booking.ref, channel: "whatsapp" });
  window.open(url, "_blank");
}

function _contactSupport(booking, staffContact) {
  const phone = staffContact?.whatsapp_phone;
  if (!phone) return;
  const text = `Bonjour, j'ai besoin d'aide concernant ma réservation ${booking.ref}.`;
  const url = `https://wa.me/${phone.replace(/[^0-9]/g, "")}?text=${encodeURIComponent(text)}`;
  EwashLog.info("bookings.contact_support", { ref: booking.ref });
  window.open(url, "_blank");
}
```

# Why the staff phone comes from props

The PWA gets `staffContact` from the parent (App component), which holds the bootstrap response. NO hardcoding inside this component — passed in. Falls back to a default phone if not configured (out of an abundance of caution; admin should configure ASAP).

# Why "Book again" pre-fills category + service

The repeat customer scenario: "Same wash as last time". Tapping "Book again" opens the booking flow already on the recap-related steps with category and service pre-selected. Customer just confirms a date/time/location.

