# Context

When `service-worker.js` itself changes (e.g. we update the `/api/*` bypass logic), browsers that already have an old SW registered won't pick up the new one unless we change the SW's own cache name or bump a version constant. Without this, stale SWs keep serving stale assets even after deploys.

# Scope

In `mobile-app/service-worker.js`:

```js
// Bump this version constant on every SW behavior change.
// The SW lifecycle automatically activates a new version when the file content differs,
// but having an explicit constant makes the cache name predictable and the change visible.
const SW_VERSION = "2026-05-14-pwa-integration";
const CACHE_NAME = `ewash-${SW_VERSION}`;

self.addEventListener("install", (event) => {
  event.waitUntil(
    caches.open(CACHE_NAME).then((cache) => cache.addAll(CORE_ASSETS))
  );
  // Force the new SW to activate immediately instead of waiting for the page to be closed.
  self.skipWaiting();
});

self.addEventListener("activate", (event) => {
  event.waitUntil(
    caches.keys().then((keys) =>
      Promise.all(keys.filter((k) => k !== CACHE_NAME).map((k) => caches.delete(k)))
    )
  );
  // Take control of pages that were loaded under the old SW.
  return self.clients.claim();
});
```

# Why `skipWaiting` + `clients.claim`

Default SW behavior is: install new SW, wait for all tabs to close, then activate. That's safe but means users can run an old SW for days. For a PWA where the customer might keep one tab open for weeks, this is too slow.

- `skipWaiting()` activates immediately.
- `clients.claim()` makes the new SW take over already-open tabs.
- The Vercel `Cache-Control: no-store` on service-worker.js (already configured) ensures the browser revalidates the SW file itself.

# Risk

If a deploy ships a buggy SW, all tabs upgrade immediately. Mitigation: SW changes go through review like any other code; the manifest cache is small (just core assets); rollback by reverting + deploy will quickly push another version.

# Acceptance criteria

- [ ] SW_VERSION constant present and committed.
- [ ] skipWaiting + clients.claim wired up.
- [ ] Manual test: deploy a change, verify open PWA tabs upgrade automatically.

