# Context

`client_request_id` makes POST /bookings idempotent. The PWA must generate ONE crid per booking ATTEMPT (across retries) — not per click. The right moment: when the user enters the recap step for the first time. If they bounce back to edit and re-enter recap, KEEP the same crid until the booking commits.

# Scope

```js
useEffect(() => {
  if (step === "recap" && !data.clientRequestId) {
    setData((d) => Object.assign({}, d, { clientRequestId: _uuid() }));
  }
}, [step]);

function _uuid() {
  return (crypto.randomUUID ? crypto.randomUUID() : _uuidFallback());
}
function _uuidFallback() {
  // Minimal RFC4122v4 — only for ancient browsers.
  var arr = new Uint8Array(16);
  crypto.getRandomValues(arr);
  arr[6] = (arr[6] & 0x0f) | 0x40;
  arr[8] = (arr[8] & 0x3f) | 0x80;
  var hex = Array.from(arr).map(function (b) { return b.toString(16).padStart(2, "0"); }).join("");
  return hex.slice(0, 8) + "-" + hex.slice(8, 12) + "-" + hex.slice(12, 16) + "-" + hex.slice(16, 20) + "-" + hex.slice(20);
}
```

After a successful submission, clear the crid so a "Book another" flow generates a fresh one:

```js
if (step === "confirmed") {
  // Don't clear immediately — if user taps "Retour" then "Book another" right away,
  // we want a new attempt. Cleared in onDone (which resets the BookingFlow).
}
```

